parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS actuator system can cause a sudden loss of power assist in the braking system, leading to increased stopping distances and increased risk of accidents, potentially resulting in fatalities.
symptoms: Loud noise or buzzing from the dashboard
brake light
ABS
and VSC lights come on simultaneously
complete loss of braking power
brake pedal goes to the floor
and the vehicle may not stop or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic brake booster can cause a sudden loss of brake function, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, or even fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loss of brake function
requiring extreme force to slow down the vehicle
buzzer alarm sounds
numerous dashboard lights illuminate
including ABS
VSC
and brake lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, or even fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden acceleration when pressing the brakes
especially when going down an incline.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the spare tire steel cable can cause the spare tire to fall off the vehicle, creating a road hazard and potentially leading to serious accidents, especially if it occurs on the highway.
symptoms: The spare tire falls off the vehicle
the spare tire is no longer securely held in place
the steel cable is broken or damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty spare tire mounting system can cause the spare tire to become dislodged, creating a road hazard and potentially leading to serious accidents.
symptoms: The spare tire is not securely held in place
the spare tire falls off the vehicle
the spare tire mounting system is damaged or broken.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the spare tire cable can cause the spare tire to separate from the vehicle, potentially leading to accidents or injuries, especially if the spare tire becomes a road hazard or obstructs traffic.
symptoms: The spare tire suddenly detaches from the vehicle
often with a loud noise or sudden jolt
and may fall off while driving
potentially causing damage to the vehicle or other objects.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the vehicle skid control system can cause the front wheel to lock up at low speeds, making it difficult to control the vehicle, and potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or even rollovers.
symptoms: The front wheel locks up at low speeds
making it impossible to clear intersections
objects and passengers are violently thrown forward
warning lights for ABS and VSC come on
wheels lock up at highway speeds
putting the vehicle in danger of rollover accidents.
